						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Oh, can't the GBA actually do both &quot;box&quot; and &quot;line&quot; modes? (Wait you just said that. I'm an idiot...) (The Genesis would have a really hard time with box mode using 24x24 sized sprites...)<br /></div><br /><br />Let's use proper terminology (because I had a hard time figuring out what either you or tepples were talking about). I dunno about the SNES or Genesis, but in GBAland, we call these modes 1 dimensional (sprite tiles are in a &quot;line&quot; in memory) or 2 dimensional (sprite tiles are in a &quot;box&quot; in memory). The GBA could do both, however, you could not mix and match (well you <strong>could</strong> with HBlanks and some nifty programming, but generally no).</div>

